Text document

Document wrapper around generated text to be sent as a file to Antidot Back Office.

Constructor Detail

TextDocument

public TextDocument(java.lang.String content)
Constructs text document.

Content type of the document is set to ContentType#APPLICATION_OCTET_STREAM by default.
Filename is automatically generated to store the document on PaF side.

Parameters:
content - [in] document content.

TextDocument

public TextDocument(java.lang.String content,
                    ContentType contentType)
Constructs text document with specific content type.

It is highly discouraged to use enumerated values from ContentType for textual content such as XML. In fact, ContentType.APPLICATION_XML force charset to ISO-8859-1.

Parameters:
content - [in] document content.
contentType - [in] content type of the document.

TextDocument

public TextDocument(java.lang.String filename,
                    java.lang.String content,
                    ContentType contentType)
Constructs document with specific filename and content type.

Content type of the document is set to ContentType#APPLICATION_OCTET_STREAM by default.

It is highly discouraged to use enumerated values from ContentType for textual content such as XML. In fact, ContentType.APPLICATION_XML force charset to ISO-8859-1.

Parameters:
filename - [in] storage name of the document.
content - [in] document content.
contentType - [in] content type of the document.
